other you?<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />You'd probably get sued for everything you have.  If that in and of itself didnt put you right out of business, once word got out that your product killed or maimed people you'd be pretty well done for, dontcha think?<br /><br />(THINK being the key word in all of this)<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br /><br />BEsides, I didnt ASK for the FDA, I didnt AGREE to PAY for their "service."<br /><br />How bout tomorrow I come knock on your door and inform you that hereafter I will be "testing" all your food.  ANything I dont deem worthy I'm going to prohibit you and your family from eating, or even posessig in your home.  You can only have what I say is kosher.  Failuer to obey will result in being kidnapped and locked in my basement.  Furthermore, I'll be billing you for this "service" as I see fit, and no, you can't refuse my service.  Its for your own good, you see, and refusal to cooperate will land you in said basement, or, if ya wanna push it, a visit from some jackbooted thugs with guns and incendiaries.  Sorry, I'm not impressed with your example.<br /><br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Well, this is quite extreme, so let's go the opposite in extreme while we're at it.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Thats not extreme in the least bit; how bout you explain to me how that's not EXACTLY how it is?  The State "informs" you that it's providing "services" for you whether you like them or not, and that it'll be billing you for those services at it sees fit.  In addition to bringing to bear the threat of force or imprisonment against those who refuse to comply, it refuses to