 apparently assume that everyone lives the way you do.  You've probably never met someone that isn't on city water, or that can look out their window and not see asphalt or another building.  It's apparently inconceivable to you that plenty of people live (just fine) in a manner that is nothing like how you live your life, yet you think you have all the answers and know exactly what it's like evreywhere in the world.  I don't even know where the nearest fire hydrant  IS, but I can assure you it's several miles away.<br /><br />That kind of "everywhere must be like here, and if it aint it should be" attitude is exactly what's wrong with this country.<br /><br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />In this, you've just shot your whole argument.  You should quit while you're ahead.  You tout how "self sufficient" you are living out in the boonies, needing no help from any outside source.  Guess what?  Not everyone wants to live in a vermin infested shack in the middle of nowhere.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Who said I live in a vermin infested shack?  But you DO make an excellent point for me: You're right, not everyone wants to.  I think people should be able to live however they want, and even pay for whatever services they want.  Guess what? Not everyone wants to pay overinflated charges for unwanted services, or services that they might be able to get cheaper and better from competitors to the State monopoly on said services.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />What might work for you, "living off the land" isn't going to work for the vast majority of the US population.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Why are you stuck on this "living off the land" thing? Believe it or not, we DO have grocery stores and running water out here.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />Apparently you're too stupid to figure out that society <b>needs</b> rules, <b>needs</b> a government in order to function properly.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />I agree 100% that society needs rules, and have posted in great depth on the subject in the OT forum.  You should read up on my political theory before trying to attack it.<br /><br />My contention, however (and the contention of many others, some far more educated than I) is that a free market would do a much better job of providing most services that the State currently holds an artificial monopoly on.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />The only reason you can live your worthless lifestyle is because other people work to make up your slack.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Take up my slack to provide me with what?  And who's fault is that?  <br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br /> Sorry your fire fighters are just going to have to use their personal vehicles to ferry water back and forth from their homes.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />No different than my tax-paying neighbors.  Aww shucks.<br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />You may think you're cool because you don't pay taxes, you're not, you're a thief, and a loser in every sense of the words.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />The State is a thief, and you are both its willing victim and it's accomplice.  You are its stooge; I, on the other hand, am a real American trying to promote capitalism.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />Please, do society a favor and kill yourself.<br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Wow, you're a real intellectual giant.<br /><br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />No, seriously, you contribute nothing to society, in fact you detract from it.  The world would be a better place if you were dead.<br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />What do you do for society?  Pay your taxes? So did Ted Bundy.<br /><br />At least I'm offering equitable, cost-effective alternatives.  I don't see you trying to argue for or demonstrate that the bloated State-monopoly on services really makes people better off, I see you hurling insults about hillbillies and vermin-infested shacks.  I don't think that's doing much to prove me wrong.<br /><br /><br /><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
