e on mars because the fuckheads mixed up metrics and feet. <br /><br /> <blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"> I went to a "private" college (ITT and some time at TN Institute of Electronics), and I paid for it. Interestingly, those schools aren't a cesspool of liberalism (i.e. socialism) like state universities are. Wonder why?<br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Probably because you went to basically a trade school.  You went to an electronics school.  You didn't go to a university so you didn't have to take other courses that breed liberalism and didnt have classmates that were majoring in them (art, english, philosophy, etc)<br /><br /> <blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">I don't need "protection under the constitution" and neither do you. We're human beings with GOD-GIVEN rights to life and liberty. Constitutions are among those things that seek to curtail such god-given rights. There's the fundamental flaw in your thinking, in my humble opinion.<br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Your opinion means shit to me, sorry to tell you.  Your thinking is hugely flawed.  The only god-given rights you have (provided you are indeed religious which makes your lack of social charity that much more humorous) are to live until you die.  Without law and punishment in place to check things, you die when someone else decides to kill you.  Don't think so?  Read some history.  Even with governments in place, people still got away with murder and even the governments did.  The "rights" you claim to have are given and protected by the people around you and by the government that protects their rights and punishes them should they break them.  I don't think you're so stupid as to think that if the whole government collapsed and people were left to their own devices, that we'd all just decide to be kind and civil to each other...just because.  <br /><br />Let's face it, man.  You're a loser who makes a miniscule income and dug up some radical ideas to try to find loopholes around income taxes because you don't want to give up what little money you have.  YOu've made sure you have nothing of value to take from you.  Don't give me any moralistic babble, I'm not that stupid.  You just want more of your own money, fuck everybody else.  Period.  Like I said, go for it.  But don't you dare use any of the public services that are paid for by taxes to which you do not contribute.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
